<h3>Reminders</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Must play all treasures before using any buys, cannot play additional treasures after buying a card</li>
    <li>Once a card/event has been bought, no additional treasures may be played</li>
    <li>Buy <b>then</b> gain, then on-gain effect will trigger while the new card is in your discard pile</li>
    <li>Trader reaction: you do not "gain" the silver, instead you "gain" the original card (which is then exchange for silver)</li>
</ul>

<h3>5-6 player</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Combine basic treasure card piles from Dominion and Intrigue</li>
    <li>Provinces: 15 for 5p, 18 for 6p</li>
    <li>Victory piles are still 8 cards for 2p and 12 cards for all other player counts</li>
    <li>Game end requires provinces or <b>four</b> empty supply piles</li>
</ul>

<!-- Duration -->
<h3>Durations</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Not discarded during cleanup if they have something left to do</li>
    <li>Stay in play until cleanup of the last turn in which they have something to do</li>
    <li>If a duration is played multiple times (e.g. Throne Room), that other card also stays in play until the Duration is discarded</li>
</ul>

<!-- Events -->
<h3>Events</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Can buy the event during buy phase, using up a buy</li>
    <li>Do the effect on the card, but event card stays on the table</li>
    <li>The same event can be bought multiple times on the same turn (with enough +buy)</li>
    <li>Cannot play more treasures after buying an event</li>
    <li>Not considered "buying a card" so cards that trigger "after buy" do not trigger after buying an event</li>
    <li>Event costs are not reduced by cost-reducers</li>
</ul>

<!-- Split Piles -->
<h3>Split Piles</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Cheaper card on top during setup</li>
    <li>May only buy or gain the card showing</li>
    <li>If a card returns to the pile, it may cover up the other type</li>
    <li>Pile can be in non-conventional order from cards that return other cards to the supply</li>
    <li>Cards that reference cost/type of a pile as if 1 card: go with what is on randomizer card</li>
    <li>Any reference to cards from a particular pile work on all cards from split pile
        <ul>
            <li>tokens from Adventures</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Empty top half of pile does not count toward empty piles</li>
    <li>2-player: use 1 of each castle, otherwiese use all</li>
    <li>Rotate: take the card(s) on top (by name) and place them on bottom of the pile
        <ul>
            <li>can also rotate Castles (Empires) or Knights (Dark Ages) or Ruins (Dark Ages)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<!-- Coffers -->
<h3>Coffers</h3>
<ul>
    <li>When instructed, add a token to coffers mat</li>
    <li>Any number of coffers can be discarded for +1 coin</li>
    <li>"Take a coin token" means +1 coffer</li>
    <li>Can only be used during buy phase or when instructed (not during Black Market buy)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Unusual Costs</h3>
<ul>
    <li>When they change cost, all copies change cost everywhere for all purposes
        <ul>
            <li>Governor (other players use same cost as you)</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><b>Can</b> change cost in the middle of resolving effects</li>
    <li>"When you buy" rules happen before actually gaining the card</li>
    <li>Range "$3 to $6" will never include cards with debt or potion costs</li>
    <li>"Up to $5" will not include cards with debt or potion costs</li>
    <li>Cost of $X really means $X + 0 potion + 0 debt</li>
</ul>

<h3>Landscape Cards</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Maximum 1 Ally (with any number of Liaison cards from Allies)</li>
    <li>Maximum 2 Events / Landmarks / Projects / Ways / Traits, but never 2 Ways</li>
</ul>

<br /><br /><br /><br />

<!-- Prosperity -->
<h3>Prosperity</h3>
<h4>Platinum/Colony</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Use both or neither</li>
    <li>Randomizer to decide whether to include</li>
    <li>Empty colony pile triggers game end</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<!-- Dark Ages -->
<h3>Dark Ages</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Shelters: Randomizer to decide whether to include</li>
    <li>Cultist, Death Cart, Marauder: include 10(N-1) ruins cards</li>
    <li>Knights: entire deck is shuffled</li>
</ul>

