<!-- Renaissance -->
<h3>Renaissance</h3>

<h4>Villagers</h4>
<ul>
    <li>When instructed, add a token to villager mat</li>
    <li>Any number of villagers can be discarded for +1 action</li>
</ul>

<h4>Projects</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Buy a project during buy phase, it uses up a buy</li>
    <li>Place your cube on card when buying it, you have that ability for rest of game</li>
    <li>Cannot place 2 cubes on same project</li>
    <li>Cannot remove a cube from a project</li>
    <li>Cubes don't block other players' cubes</li>
    <li>Buying a project is not "buying a card" and cost reducers have no effect</li>
    <li>Cannot buy a project while you have debt</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<!-- Menagerie -->
<h3>Menagerie</h3>

<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4>Exile</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>"Exile a card" = put it on exile mat</li>
                <li>Include exiled cards for scoring</li>
                <li>When gaining a card, may discard other copies from exile mat
                    <ul>
                        <li>all or none</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Exiling a card from the supply does not count as "gaining" the card</li>
                <li>Discarding a card from the exile mat <b>does</b> count as discarding it</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4>Ways</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>All actions can instead be used as the Way</li>
                <li>Text below dividing lines still applies</li>
                <li>Can use the Way instead of Enchantress +1 Card/+1 Action effect</li>
                <li>Cards played at an unusual time can be used as Ways</li>
                <li>For action repeaters, choose for each instance whether to use Way</li>
                <li>For a Duration played multiple times, each can be a Way
                    <ul>
                        <li>at least 1 must be the Duration in order to stay in play</li>
                        <li>track the tallies for Duration vs Way</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>Tokens from Adventures still apply when using the card as a Way</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>



<hr />

<!-- Allies -->
<h3>Allies</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Required when there is a Liaison card</li>
    <li>Players start with 1 favor token (5 if using Importer)</li>
    <li>Use 1 Ally per game, even with multiple Liaisons</li>
    <li>Add coin tokens to Favor mat to identify them as favors</li>
    <li>Spending favors may be done once per favor window, unless it specifies repeat as desired</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<!-- Plunder -->
<h3>Plunder</h3>
<h4>Loot</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Shuffle loot deck face down</li>
    <li>"Gain a loot" means gain top card of loot pile, revealing to all players</li>
</ul>

<h4>Traits</h4>
<ul>
    <li>Choose a random <b>Action</b> or <b>Treasure</b> kingdom pile and put a Trait on it</li>
    <li>Max 1 trait per pile</li>
    <li>Affects all the cards from the split pile</li>
    <li>Traits continue even when the pile is empty</li>
</ul>
